A vintage-style illustration of an antique wooden card catalog with dozens of small brass-handled drawers, each drawer labeled with ornate tags showing a clear hierarchical system. Some drawers are pulled open at different depths, revealing neatly organized index cards in varying colors sorted by category. The scene is bathed in warm amber light from a green banker's lamp nearby, casting soft shadows across the rich mahogany wood grain. Dust motes float in the air, and a magnifying glass rests beside the cabinet. The composition emphasizes the satisfying order and structure of the filing system, with visual hierarchy shown through the drawer arrangements stepping back in organized rows like a cityscape of perfect organization.
